ShadowFM commented on #502 FR - Upload also to Dropbox Enterprise possible [NOT YET PLANED|doob]

You may not believe it, but there are no limits, except that the size of a file must not exceed 100GB. There is an API that is limited to 20.000.000 accesses per day, but this is not used for rclone. An upload limit as with Google (750GB/day) does not exist with the Dropbox subscription, you can really upload as much as you want, currently I also move my library from Google to Dropbox and migrate per day about 7TB, and not with detours of service accounts or similar but just pure uploading. Initially, the Dropbox cloud has a size of 3TB, but this is automatically increased as soon as a used storage of 80% is reached, if necessary, you can also contact support and have the storage expanded. I have contacted the support and initially expanded by 200TB, this went without problems. Dropbox is integrated into rclone like Google, should the desire exist also as Encrypted variant what works great. Should you otherwise continue to use rclone then I would make the adjustments in the rclone config, that would not be an issue for me if another provider is to be integrated.
